THE RISK (context, do not rewrite): perturbation [{"nodeId":"cust.distributor","op":"exclude","note":"Distributor cell closed until next line-review cycle — outside the Year-1 window"},{"nodeId":"obtainableFactor","op":"scale","value":0.7,"note":"Distribution-routed mid-market deals slip beyond Year 1, dragging the blended ramp below the 3% mid-band"}], likelihood 0.3, category execution

FIELDS TO REWRITE:
{
 "title": "Annual line reviews and exclusivity terms lock the distribution channel for the launch year",
 "narrative": "The distributor cell (13%) and much of the mid/enterprise cell (25%) are reached through master distributors and reseller networks — the MaxPower model, where the distributor sells to resellers, not end customers. Those distributors run annual line reviews: category slots are allocated once a year, often with exclusivity or MDF commitments to the incumbent PDU line, and intelligent-PDU buyer guides note distributors already carry OEM/private-label options that fill the 'value' slot. A pre-launch entrant arrives mid-cycle into a category that is already filled twice over. The result is not a lower win rate — it is that the indirect channel produces zero Year-1 revenue while the model quietly assumes it contributes at the same 3% pace as everything else.",
 "mechanism": [
  {
   "step": "trigger",
   "text": "CE power-infrastructure distribution operates on the master-distributor model with annual line reviews; category slots for rack power are held by incumbent lines and supplemented by private-label ODM options the distributor already controls",
   "refs": [
    "digest:cust-mix#c8",
    "digest:cust-mix#c13",
    "ledger:cust.distributor"
   ]
  },
  {
   "step": "propagation",
   "text": "An entrant launching mid-cycle cannot obtain a line-card slot until the next review, and no corpus source quantifies indirect share or documents off-cycle onboarding — the mid/enterprise cell that buys through these resellers is similarly delayed, pushing all distribution-routed deals beyond the 12-month window",
   "refs": [
    "profile:Stage",
    "digest:cust-mix#c4",
    "ledger:cust.operator-mid"
   ]
  },
  {
   "step": "model-impact",
   "text": "cust.distributor (0.13) is unavailable for Year 1 and the blended Year-1 pace across remaining cells falls below the 3% mid-band, because the funnel applies one obtainableFactor uniformly across channels with radically different onboarding clocks",
   "refs": [
    "ledger:cust.distributor",
    "ledger:obtainableFactor"
   ]
  }
 ],
 "whyMissable": "Distribution looks like the easy channel — low share (0.13), low stakes, 'we'll sign a distributor when ready.' The kill detail is timing, not access: the ledger has no time dimension on buyer cells, so a channel that is open in month 14 and one that is open in month 1 look identical in the funnel.",
 "falsifier": "A named CE power/IT-infrastructure distributor signs the venture's line off-cycle within 6 months of launch without exclusivity conflict — or documented evidence that CE distributors onboard new PDU vendors on rolling rather than annual review calendars.",
 "likelihoodRationale": "Annual line reviews with category exclusivity are standard practice in electrical/IT distribution (base rate of the channel model), but some challenger distributors deliberately onboard new lines off-cycle to differentiate [evidence revision: The trigger (master-distributor model, filled category slots, private-label value option) is confirmed, but the falsifier is partially met: multiple named IT/power-infrastructure distributors publicly onboarded new PDU/power vendors as standalone agreements across 2025-2026, and line-review governance sources note rolling calendars rather than strict single annual windows. This weakens the strong 'zero Year-1 indirect revenue' claim, lowering likelihood from 0.4 toward 0.3. It is not fully refuted because the evidence does not directly document off-cycle onboarding in the specific CE market with no exclusivity conflict, nor that these deals closed within 6 months of a vendor's launch.]"
}

Emit JSON: { title, narrative, mechanism: [{step, text, refs}], whyMissable, falsifier, likelihoodRationale }
